Using packages

  (On terminal) npm init
    Do the steps you are given
    
  (On package.json) set up "start"
    npm start
    
  Google npmjs
  
  Downloading a package though terminal, by "npm install (package name)"

  (On package.json) You are able to check what packages are used to the project

  node_modules & package-lock.json are patched automatically

  package-lock.json = Library that indicates what packages downloaded in what version
  
   const randomcolor = require("randomcolor");
 
   let color1 = randomcolor();
   let color2 = randomcolor();
   let color3 = randomcolor();
 
   console.log(color1, color2, color3);
